TextBlock.TextLine: if I knew upon what string the mode will runn this yeare could in ord. more spanish
cloathes yett you have orders for 2 bales more, for which take yd. owne time I am
heantely sorry, that you feare to accomplish the desire of the good fathers, sure then
J.K. is to hard for you, & Roosendael here with him, to tye him p to them selves
& so to spoile mij undertakeings here: butt can you not prevaile: take what measures
there is to be found, that I may have att least 5 broad lift, as soone as possible, for
I promised to deliver them about easter, & then 5 more about the latter end of may
& 5 more about august or sber so I shall want 20 a yeare: pray lett mee not be
last att, & underminde J.K. for hie doth itt to yd. governo, I would rether have you
go to him in the countrey, then to be imdon in my word. wish time & opportunitie
shall endeavour to promote yd. intrest so setenall here, though verspaes returning
will be some hinderance. I have a small cond. forom m. sealy to buy cloverseeds
which adens are vere neare compleated, my thancks for yd recomandation, itt may
give cause for a greater for the future. I do much want the drap coollours northrer
bayes, & the forman norshrens so that I hope some thing will come with Pindar -
you maij give m. hill the last orders, for I doubt he will do best in the fynest soort
butt the draps must be lively non y allowish, butt blewisch & white, & better then the
patt. sent, pray advises how you supposes goods will rule about june & Juliy to take my
measures accordingley
Dubln m. Elnathan Lumm
I have before mee yd. aggreable of 7 past, I hope that the last easterly winds
have brought over the laces, which I should be vere gladd to understand, for thin I
doubt not butt I shall finde yd. orders for more, beeng well assureed that they be bought
att all the advantidge that can be exspected in that trade. I shall with all speed provide
the broad lace, & send you as formerly, & finde the vallew on m. de Hulter & va m
LEpon mr. Will. Lobb

I have in 2 time recd. yd of 11th past, according to which do exspect the patt. & invoyce
of the serges in ordered, if either of the vessel in loading att dopsom be still there, I could
wish to have by them, a bale with 12 drap collours cloth serges, or sparrow grayes of a
lively cullour much upon the string of the inclosed patt. add to them 6 or 8 fyne 24 yd
serges of the same cullour, butt in case they can not be dispatched by either of the vessels
ready, then I would have finst yd. advise how the com to in order more goods
accordingly, yett I am somewhat in haste for these, whilst I exspect yd advise
